{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17566562","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17566562"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T23:43:55+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T23:43:55+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18846"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18846","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18846"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.08,0.1,0.54,0.13,0.16]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11579"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"79685"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11579","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11579"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18846"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"64989"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"18"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"11259"},{"type":"tags","id":"11260"},{"type":"tags","id":"11301"},{"type":"tags","id":"12867"},{"type":"tags","id":"12918"},{"type":"tags","id":"12921"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"27249"},{"type":"contributions","id":"27250"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"79685","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/79685"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA junior doctor prescribes penicillin for a patient whose notes document a previous mild rash with amoxicillin. The error is identified by the pharmacist before administration. The patient is anxious and has previously made formal complaints about their care.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the most appropriate professional response to this situation?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Discuss with supervisor and document without patient disclosure","Report incident after discussing with pharmacist and patient","Complete an incident report and disclose to the patient with a senior colleague","Inform patient immediately and submit incident report afterwards","Document error and arrange formal team meeting for disclosure"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe most appropriate response is to \u003Cstrong\u003Ecomplete an incident report and disclose to the patient with a senior colleague\u003C/strong\u003E. This fulfills the duty of candour while ensuring the disclosure is handled appropriately given the patient\u0027s anxiety and history of complaints. It demonstrates professional integrity while maintaining a structured approach to error management.\u003C/p\u003E        \u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect responses are problematic because:\u003C/p\u003E        \u003Cul\u003E        \u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDiscuss with supervisor and document without patient disclosure\u003C/strong\u003E - This breaches the duty of candour and transparency requirements\u003C/li\u003E        \u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EReport incident after discussing with pharmacist and patient\u003C/strong\u003E - While involving relevant parties, this sequence delays formal reporting and lacks senior support\u003C/li\u003E        \u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EInform patient immediately and submit incident report afterwards\u003C/strong\u003E - Immediate disclosure without senior support may be poorly handled given the patient\u0027s anxiety\u003C/li\u003E        \u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDocument error and arrange formal team meeting for disclosure\u003C/strong\u003E - This unnecessarily delays disclosure and over-formalizes the response\u003C/li\u003E    \u003C/ul\u003E        \u003Cp\u003EProfessional error management requires prompt reporting, appropriate documentation, and transparent disclosure while considering timing, context, and support needs. This maintains trust while contributing to systemic improvement in patient safety.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Medical professionals have a duty of candour requiring open disclosure of errors, including near-misses, to patients and the healthcare team.","Error reporting systems aim to identify systemic issues and prevent future incidents rather than assign individual blame.","Professional integrity requires balancing transparency with appropriate timing and manner of disclosure to maintain patient trust."],"references":["Medical Board of Australia. Good medical practice: a code of conduct for doctors in Australia [online]. 2020 [Cited 2025 Jan 15]. Available at: https://www.medicalboard.gov.au/codes-guidelines-policies/code-of-conduct.aspx","Hart JL. Deception, honesty, and professionalism: A persistent challenge in modern medicine. Curr Opin Psychol. 2022 Oct;47:101434. doi: 10.1016/j.copsyc.2022.101434. Epub 2022 Jul 31. PMID: 35998527. Available from: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/35998527/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"64989"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18846"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"64989","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/64989"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-15T12:57:02+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-15T12:58:12+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11579"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"79685"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"18","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/18"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\uddd1\u200d\u2696\ufe0f","name":"Medicolegal","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{